reviews.review_text:
3.7 stars A very high-quality performance with a lot of deliberateness and soul for a time period I'm not generally fond of. Mike Kutik is obviously a galactic hitchhiker who knows where his towel is, judging by this awesome recording, which I find far easier to listen to than any of the soundboards or even his own matrix copy: indeed, this is my favorite copy of this recording to date, and not just because I can still download it.

It could be said that the set list is overshadowed by that of the previous night (Cryptical et al.). However, it is actually pretty boring as set lists go, with the only star appearance--Might As Well--marred by a sloppy rendition in an otherwise pretty well-played set.
